02:54.521 --> 02:56.689
Won't forget!

02:56.724 --> 02:58.491
Never forget!

02:58.525 --> 03:00.893
[Indistinct shouting] Timothy:
The prosecution has to prove

03:00.928 --> 03:03.363
that likely your brother did
what he's been accused of.

03:03.397 --> 03:05.765
And if they can't, the case is dismissed.

03:05.799 --> 03:06.666
Yes.

03:06.700 --> 03:08.935
Now, they do have compelling evidence...

03:08.969 --> 03:10.937
Mr. Tontz's testimony.

03:10.971 --> 03:13.539
- They have the gun now.
- <i>A</i> gun, not Carter's gun.

03:13.574 --> 03:16.342
- They can't put a gun in his hand.
- That works for us.

03:16.377 --> 03:18.911
So do the mistakes they
made with the DNA evidence,

03:18.946 --> 03:20.847
a lack of an eyewitness to the crime.

03:20.881 --> 03:22.882
There's as good of a chance

03:22.916 --> 03:24.751
the judge will dismiss the
case as carry it forward.

03:24.785 --> 03:28.388
The rally put a lot of
pressure on these people.

03:28.422 --> 03:30.423
Never forget!

03:33.093 --> 03:35.094
[Indistinct shouting in distance]

03:45.172 --> 03:47.206
[Buzzer]

04:21.141 --> 04:23.142
[Birds chirping]

04:37.124 --> 04:38.691
[Blade snaps]

04:38.725 --> 04:41.694
[Sighs]

04:41.728 --> 04:43.663
[Inhales deeply]

05:10.924 --> 05:12.959
[Clattering]

05:15.662 --> 05:17.997
[Clatter]

05:18.031 --> 05:20.032
[Sighs]

05:34.715 --> 05:36.682
Hmm.

05:53.133 --> 05:55.168
[Ignition clicks, gas hisses]

06:41.448 --> 06:44.217
[Strumming off-key chords]
♪ Don't call me Kevin ♪

06:44.251 --> 06:46.252
♪ dude, my name be Devon ♪

06:46.286 --> 06:47.887
[laughter]

06:47.921 --> 06:50.990
♪ I come from Wisconsin ♪

06:51.024 --> 06:53.426
♪ but I ain't got no Johnson ♪

06:53.460 --> 06:55.461
[laughter] Devon: All right, Edgar.
That's enough.

06:55.495 --> 06:57.897
- Come on.
- Hey, I'm releasing my frustration.

06:57.931 --> 06:59.465
I'm "inspired."

06:59.499 --> 07:01.133
[Laughter]

07:01.168 --> 07:02.134
Hey, don't grudge him, man.

07:02.169 --> 07:04.637
Hey, what rhymes with,
uh, "Devon got no..."?

07:04.671 --> 07:06.138
"Devon think he slick."

07:06.173 --> 07:07.740
"Devon got no chick."

07:07.774 --> 07:09.742
Both: 'Cause Devon got no...

07:09.776 --> 07:11.310
[Laughter] Nelson: Hey, settle down.

07:11.345 --> 07:13.112
Devon: I've got it.
That's enough, all right?

07:13.146 --> 07:15.414
- Hey... off, man.
- You need to settle down.

07:15.449 --> 07:18.317
Come on. That's enough. Just... just give...

07:18.352 --> 07:21.187
[Murmuring]

07:21.221 --> 07:22.989
Yo, you better stay back!

07:23.023 --> 07:25.124
Take a knee. Put it down. Take a knee.

07:25.158 --> 07:27.126
Man: Hey, put it down right now!

07:27.160 --> 07:29.295
Man ♪2: Come on, man. Come on.

07:29.329 --> 07:30.930
- Let it go.
- Oh, you want to play, too?

07:30.964 --> 07:32.365
[Indistinct shouting] Try me!

07:32.399 --> 07:34.133
All right. Put the guitar down!

07:34.167 --> 07:36.135
No, try me! Try... Hey!

07:36.169 --> 07:39.105
Stay back! Clear the room!
Clear the room now!

07:39.139 --> 07:40.973
Get them out of here!

07:41.008 --> 07:42.508
[Grunting]

07:42.542 --> 07:43.809
Get them out!

07:45.212 --> 07:46.345
Tony: Stop.

07:46.380 --> 07:49.115
[Indistinct shouting]

07:49.149 --> 07:52.952
Stop! [Indistinct shouting]

07:52.986 --> 07:54.020
Get them out of here!

07:54.054 --> 07:55.788
Turn him. Turn him. Let's go.

07:55.822 --> 07:57.723
1, 2, 3.

08:08.684 --> 08:12.053
First time I came in here, I
wasn't supposed to be here.

08:12.088 --> 08:14.456
People knew that.

08:14.490 --> 08:16.491
They treated me like a punk.

08:16.525 --> 08:19.060
Treated me like that 'cause I was one.

08:19.095 --> 08:23.898
And second time I came here,
I wasn't a punk no more.

08:23.933 --> 08:25.867
Felt good.

08:25.901 --> 08:27.869
Ain't lying.

08:27.903 --> 08:32.307
People look at me, 16, like I am respect.

08:32.341 --> 08:34.909
I've always respected you.

08:34.943 --> 08:38.313
You were proud. That's different.

08:38.347 --> 08:41.916
So I got respect.

08:41.951 --> 08:45.920
[Scoffs] I earned my respect.

08:45.955 --> 08:48.089
You're my son, Antonio.

08:48.124 --> 08:51.893
And you will always be my son.

08:51.927 --> 08:54.329
I love you no matter what.

08:54.363 --> 08:56.898
So you... y-you can push me away,

08:56.932 --> 08:59.868
but I'm not going away.

09:00.703 --> 09:03.138
I'm here.

09:07.443 --> 09:10.045
<i>Papi, I need you to get me out.</i>

09:10.079 --> 09:11.846
<i>Papi,</i> I ain't gonna make it here.

09:11.881 --> 09:13.248
- They killed Edgar.
- Who?

09:13.282 --> 09:16.084
I'm not gonna make it
if they send me to jail.

09:16.118 --> 09:17.052
I'm talking to the lawyer.

09:17.086 --> 09:19.187
I'm trying to get them to review the case.

09:19.221 --> 09:21.022
Do something else!

09:21.057 --> 09:25.193
What? What can I do?

09:25.227 --> 09:27.595
I need you to do more.

09:27.630 --> 09:29.664
Ohh.

09:43.779 --> 09:46.882
[Siren wailing in distance]

09:48.284 --> 09:50.051
[Knock on door]

09:50.086 --> 09:52.053
[Train whistle blows in distance]

09:52.088 --> 09:53.688
Hector: Adela.

09:53.723 --> 09:56.091
<i>Es papi.</i>

09:57.793 --> 10:01.963
<i>Está bien, Adela. Es papi.</i>

10:01.998 --> 10:05.033
Adela. <i>Ven.</i>

10:05.067 --> 10:08.837
<i>Mija. Ven.</i>

10:13.809 --> 10:16.945
<i>ÿSiempre te dejan salir así?</i>

10:16.979 --> 10:20.315
Lo hacen porque necesitan <i>mi testimonio.</i>

10:20.349 --> 10:24.586
<i>Oyes mija, tu papi es alguien importante.</i>

10:26.355 --> 10:28.323
[Chuckles]

10:28.357 --> 10:30.325
Nunca me contestaste.

10:30.359 --> 10:31.393
<i>ÿDe qué?</i>

10:31.427 --> 10:34.663
You want to talk about
America, talk in English.

10:34.697 --> 10:36.665
Adela doesn't need to hear it.

10:36.699 --> 10:37.899
We could be together, you know.

10:37.934 --> 10:39.100
I could get a job.

10:39.135 --> 10:41.937
What kind?

10:41.971 --> 10:42.938
Technology.

10:42.972 --> 10:44.139
[Chuckles] What? I can.

10:44.173 --> 10:46.775
I-I'm not gonna fail this time.

10:46.809 --> 10:50.812
You didn't fail before. You just gave up.

10:51.981 --> 10:54.783
What about getting married?

10:54.817 --> 10:55.717
I mean, we get married,

10:55.752 --> 10:57.552
you guys could come with
me... You and Adela.

10:57.587 --> 11:00.422
It would take us seven years
for us to get our citizenship.

11:00.456 --> 11:01.823
It's all gonna work out.

11:01.858 --> 11:03.992
It's been five years since you ran off.

11:04.026 --> 11:06.595
Now I'm supposed to wait around seven more?

11:06.629 --> 11:07.662
W-well, we...

11:07.697 --> 11:10.165
We'll get some place in
the mountains. I mean, us.

11:10.199 --> 11:12.801
Get a place in the mountains and get married

11:12.835 --> 11:14.970
and you get a technology job...

11:15.004 --> 11:18.407
Can it ever be regular for you?

11:18.441 --> 11:19.808
This is regular.

11:19.842 --> 11:21.810
No. No.

11:21.844 --> 11:23.979
It's regular for other people.

11:24.013 --> 11:27.983
Regular for you would be staying
out of trouble for six months.

11:28.017 --> 11:31.420
Regular for you would
be buying a decent shirt

11:31.454 --> 11:33.622
and going to work on the first day.

11:35.224 --> 11:38.427
Why you always trying to make it so big?

11:38.461 --> 11:40.796
Why can't you just please try

11:40.830 --> 11:43.832
to do some regular... Okay?

11:43.866 --> 11:46.334
It's all gonna work.

11:46.369 --> 11:48.937
It's all gonna work out.

11:48.971 --> 11:50.338
Come on, <i>papi.</i>

11:50.373 --> 11:52.541
Eat it.

11:52.575 --> 11:55.010
[Chuckles] [Inhales deeply]

11:55.044 --> 11:57.879
[Gulps] [Giggles]

11:57.914 --> 11:59.047
[Indistinct conversations]

11:59.081 --> 12:02.651
[Door opens, closes]

12:02.685 --> 12:05.220
Ruth: I came here because

12:05.254 --> 12:07.222
you and I actually have a lot in common.

12:07.256 --> 12:08.657
We do?

12:08.691 --> 12:11.860
We both want what's best for our families.

12:11.894 --> 12:14.463
I-I know we have competing agendas...

12:14.497 --> 12:16.231
That doesn't even begin
to describe what's...

12:16.265 --> 12:20.669
I know. I know that. But I...

12:20.703 --> 12:22.671
Is there someplace we can talk in private?

12:22.705 --> 12:24.039
No.

12:24.073 --> 12:25.674
[Inhales deeply]

12:25.708 --> 12:28.243
I think it would be good if my daughter

12:28.277 --> 12:30.245
and your brother weren't involved.

12:30.279 --> 12:32.247
Are we working from the same place?

12:32.281 --> 12:34.883
This is not some bad date they're on.

12:34.917 --> 12:36.051
It isn't. I-I know that.

12:36.085 --> 12:37.686
This is... [Stammers]

12:37.720 --> 12:39.254
I... [sighs]

12:39.288 --> 12:42.390
A-as much as I love Aubry, she's...

12:42.425 --> 12:45.594
Time after time, I think,

12:45.628 --> 12:48.597
"okay, she's hit bottom.

12:48.631 --> 12:50.599
She'll change."

12:50.633 --> 12:53.602
And then something else
happens, something worse.

12:53.636 --> 12:56.204
- I mean...
- From what I see,

12:56.239 --> 13:00.275
your daughter is a drug
addict and a habitual liar.

13:00.309 --> 13:04.279
And your brother is a thief and an enabler.

13:04.313 --> 13:06.882
[Sighs] However it is, it's a bad mix.

13:06.916 --> 13:10.919
For either of them to survive
this, it has to change.

13:10.953 --> 13:12.521
If you're talking about some sort

13:12.555 --> 13:15.290
of family intervention, now is not the time.

13:15.324 --> 13:18.293
No, this <i>is</i> the time.

13:18.327 --> 13:21.897
If your brother walks away
after this hearing, then what?

13:21.931 --> 13:25.300
What happens if the two
of them can be together?

13:25.334 --> 13:28.737
This is not about counseling or therapy.

13:28.771 --> 13:30.939
I need...

13:30.973 --> 13:33.742
I want you to help me
get in to see your brother.

13:33.776 --> 13:35.911
To do what?

13:35.945 --> 13:37.913
To try t...

13:37.947 --> 13:40.348
To try something.

13:50.853 --> 13:51.886
Mr. Hayes.

13:51.921 --> 13:54.623
Hayes: Oh, was Tony willing
to offer up testimony

13:54.657 --> 13:56.191
- in the Carter Nix case?
- He didn't know anything.

13:56.225 --> 13:57.626
I can talk to you son next week.

13:57.660 --> 13:58.660
No, he needs help now.

13:58.694 --> 14:00.662
And I just picked up two
more cases this morning.

14:00.696 --> 14:02.864
I have to get my son out of here, Mr. Hayes.

14:02.898 --> 14:03.665
He's hurting.

14:03.699 --> 14:06.735
He's scare... I'm talking to you!

14:08.371 --> 14:11.573
He's a good kid.

14:11.607 --> 14:13.942
I'm gonna give you some advice.

14:13.976 --> 14:15.744
And this is off the record.

14:15.778 --> 14:18.146
Get yourself a private defense attorney,

14:18.181 --> 14:20.148
someone who can focus on your son's case.

14:20.183 --> 14:21.516
You're representing him.

14:21.551 --> 14:23.752
I represent a lot of kids.

14:23.786 --> 14:25.587
I'm supposed to carry a max of 15 cases.

14:25.621 --> 14:27.589
I have 28.

14:27.623 --> 14:29.958
You need someone who can put in the hours.

14:29.992 --> 14:31.359
I can't afford that.

14:31.394 --> 14:33.762
That costs money. I don't
have that kind of money.

14:33.796 --> 14:35.530
He's your son.

14:35.565 --> 14:37.632
Get it.

14:53.049 --> 14:55.350
[Birds chirping]

14:55.384 --> 14:58.887
Barb: She was the only other person up here

14:58.921 --> 15:00.121
who was anything like a friend.

15:00.156 --> 15:01.056
And in few hours,

15:01.090 --> 15:02.958
I go from finding out she's a raging bigot

15:02.992 --> 15:04.559
to her bleeding on the street.

15:04.594 --> 15:06.561
- That's me.
- No, you're not the same.

15:06.596 --> 15:07.963
I... If I close my eyes,

15:07.997 --> 15:11.333
I see myself on the ground, bleeding.

15:11.367 --> 15:13.702
You feel what you feel for a reason,

15:13.736 --> 15:16.705
not because God told you
we need to segregate.

15:16.739 --> 15:17.706
That's perverted.

15:17.740 --> 15:19.140
- If it's perverted...
- It - it is.

15:19.175 --> 15:20.742
Well, what difference does it make

15:20.776 --> 15:22.143
how you end up there?

15:22.178 --> 15:23.345
Y-you know what the difference is?

15:23.379 --> 15:24.913
I'm in the same place she was.

15:24.947 --> 15:27.749
At least you care how you feel.

15:27.783 --> 15:29.351
At least it bothers you.

15:29.385 --> 15:31.720
And knowing that, knowing where you are,

15:31.754 --> 15:32.954
it's going to do things to you.

15:32.989 --> 15:36.658
You just have to hold on through
the preliminary examination.

15:36.692 --> 15:39.060
Why can't we just go to trial?

15:39.095 --> 15:40.695
Ugh. It's another step.

15:40.730 --> 15:43.064
It has been four months!

15:43.099 --> 15:45.500
I say that like it's forever.

15:45.535 --> 15:48.270
But it's just been four
months since I lost Matt.

15:48.304 --> 15:49.905
I...

15:51.574 --> 15:56.745
I... was tired when this whole thing began.

15:56.779 --> 15:58.847
I'm exhausted now.

15:58.881 --> 16:01.850
I'm starting to not even care
what happens anymore. [Liquid pours]

16:01.884 --> 16:05.220
I just... I want something to happen.

16:09.091 --> 16:10.625
It's for my own protection.

16:10.660 --> 16:13.261
What is?

16:13.296 --> 16:15.263
It's registered. I have a license.

16:15.298 --> 16:17.866
It's my legal right.

16:17.900 --> 16:20.468
Forget it. I'm sorry. It's just...

16:20.503 --> 16:22.704
Someone threw a brick at my car...

16:22.738 --> 16:24.472
While I was in it.

16:24.507 --> 16:28.276
You're right. I'm here to support you.

16:28.311 --> 16:30.078
I know how to use it.

16:30.112 --> 16:32.113
Good. I'm glad.

16:35.318 --> 16:36.451
Nurse: All right, Gwen.

16:36.486 --> 16:38.620
So, today, we're gonna go ahead
and take out the catheter.

16:38.654 --> 16:40.856
You're gonna feel just a
little bit of sensation.

16:40.890 --> 16:41.990
So take a deep breath in...

16:42.024 --> 16:43.792
[Gwen inhales deeply]
And go ahead and blow out.

16:43.826 --> 16:45.594
[Exhales deeply]

16:45.628 --> 16:49.631
Good. Good, good, good. That's all done.

16:49.665 --> 16:51.800
So, now, when you take her home,

16:51.834 --> 16:55.604
you can go ahead and use adult diapers

16:55.638 --> 16:57.639
- or a brief, all right?
- Okay.

16:57.673 --> 16:59.941
- If you guys want to help?
- Sure.

16:59.976 --> 17:01.576
[Tom clears throat]

17:01.611 --> 17:03.745
Okay. All right.

17:03.780 --> 17:06.580
Now, let her do what she can by herself.

17:06.616 --> 17:09.584
Okay. Good.

17:09.618 --> 17:11.987
Very good, Gwen.

17:12.021 --> 17:13.989
Now, she will need help in the bathroom,

17:14.022 --> 17:15.624
so let's go into there

17:15.657 --> 17:17.224
and let's practice a few times, okay?

17:17.260 --> 17:19.227
Yeah.

17:19.262 --> 17:22.230
Eve: We both need to learn how to do this.

17:22.265 --> 17:24.566
I mean, it's not like when she was a baby.

17:24.599 --> 17:28.170
- Diapers?
- I can't do this alone, Tom.

17:28.204 --> 17:29.771
T-there's nothing more I want

17:29.806 --> 17:31.573
than to have her home, to have her with us.

17:31.607 --> 17:33.408
- I know.
- But I need more time.

17:33.443 --> 17:37.612
There isn't any more time.
She's ready to come home.

17:37.647 --> 17:38.680
[Sighs]

17:38.714 --> 17:42.818
The things that happened,
do they really matter now?

17:42.852 --> 17:45.654
I mean it. Do they matter?

17:45.688 --> 17:48.657
That's not what bothers me.

17:48.691 --> 17:49.758
No, the past is past.

17:49.792 --> 17:51.159
And you can really say that?

17:51.194 --> 17:53.762
I say it, I mean it.

17:53.796 --> 17:56.531
I just need to figure out
what we're all about

17:56.566 --> 18:01.036
so that the same bad
choices are not repeated.

18:01.070 --> 18:04.272
Well, there really isn't any math for that.

18:04.307 --> 18:06.508
So whatever we need to figure out,

18:06.542 --> 18:08.343
let's do it.

18:08.377 --> 18:11.346
But we need to get Gwen out of this city.

18:11.380 --> 18:13.815
We need to get her home.

18:17.453 --> 18:19.154
You brought her here?

18:19.188 --> 18:20.355
You know her?

18:20.390 --> 18:21.757
Never met her.

18:21.791 --> 18:23.759
Will you talk to her?

18:23.793 --> 18:25.160
Why?

18:25.194 --> 18:27.162
Because she has something to say.

18:27.196 --> 18:29.631
I wouldn't bring her here
if I didn't feel her truth.

18:29.666 --> 18:31.300
I got nothing to say to her.

18:31.334 --> 18:34.336
Then just listen. Let her talk.

18:36.639 --> 18:38.840
Fine.

18:55.892 --> 18:57.459
Hello.

18:57.493 --> 19:00.562
How's Aubry?

19:00.596 --> 19:01.997
She's alive.

19:03.633 --> 19:05.634
Does she ask about me?

19:09.205 --> 19:12.207
Tell her, w-when all this is over,

19:12.242 --> 19:14.009
it's gonna be me and her again.

19:14.043 --> 19:16.011
I-I-I'm gonna take care of her.

19:16.045 --> 19:18.380
The way you took care of her this time?

19:18.414 --> 19:22.384
I called help for her. I
gave myself up for her.

19:22.418 --> 19:24.853
And you feel good about that?

19:24.888 --> 19:28.290
You called 911 after she was overdosing,

19:28.324 --> 19:30.859
after you got into a
fight with drug dealers.

19:30.894 --> 19:35.664
You do the little bit you can
and you're proud of yourself?

19:35.698 --> 19:38.066
The way you two are,

19:38.101 --> 19:39.868
is any of this normal or good?

19:39.903 --> 19:42.471
She's good with me.

19:42.505 --> 19:44.072
W-when we're together, we're...

19:44.107 --> 19:46.675
You're almost dead in a cheap motel.

19:46.709 --> 19:48.377
That's what you were.

19:48.411 --> 19:51.580
But you felt like a hero.

19:51.614 --> 19:54.216
You felt you did what you
had to do to save her,

19:54.250 --> 19:58.820
and it felt right trading
your life for hers.

19:58.855 --> 20:00.222
You say you love her.

20:00.256 --> 20:01.590
Look, it's not just talk.

20:01.624 --> 20:03.592
Then let her go.

20:03.626 --> 20:05.394
Be without her.

20:05.428 --> 20:06.595
She's my girl.

20:06.629 --> 20:09.831
She's my daughter.

20:09.866 --> 20:11.900
My little girl is dying.

20:11.935 --> 20:16.939
The girl you say you love is dying.

20:16.973 --> 20:21.410
Please, help me save her.

20:34.940 --> 20:38.143
Alonzo: The, uh... the ceilings,
they're... they're 12-foot high.

20:38.177 --> 20:40.145
Raul: Lot size?

20:40.179 --> 20:42.514
17,000.

20:42.548 --> 20:45.316
So you're asking for $5, $6 per?

20:45.351 --> 20:47.352
- Yes.
- Customer base?

20:47.386 --> 20:50.321
100, 200 regulars. I-I
don't have an exact count.

20:50.356 --> 20:52.357
If I take over a business
that's up and running,

20:52.391 --> 20:53.925
I want that verified.

20:53.959 --> 20:55.827
I'm happy to share the books.

20:55.861 --> 20:57.729
Not past customers. Current.

20:57.763 --> 21:00.431
I know about the problems
you've had recently.

21:00.466 --> 21:02.267
My customers are loyal.

21:02.301 --> 21:03.434
Looks pretty slow to me.

21:03.469 --> 21:06.070
It's a slow day.

21:06.105 --> 21:09.440
I'll take it off your hands for $50,000.

21:09.475 --> 21:11.276
I'm asking $90,000.

21:11.310 --> 21:15.446
As a hardworking "illegal,"
$50,000's the best I can do.

21:15.481 --> 21:17.515
[Train whistle blowing in distance]

21:19.385 --> 21:21.553
Could you go $85,000?

21:21.587 --> 21:24.389
You want to sell it fast, I'll buy it fast.

21:24.423 --> 21:26.591
$50,000, cash.

21:29.929 --> 21:33.331
Don't worry. It's not drug money.

21:40.406 --> 21:42.373
[Engine turns over]

21:42.408 --> 21:45.777
[TV chatter]

21:48.480 --> 21:51.449
[Chuckles]

21:51.483 --> 21:53.785
Oscar: So, you want some tea?

21:53.819 --> 21:56.487
Uh, a beer would be all right.

21:56.522 --> 21:57.755
Sure.

21:57.790 --> 22:00.158
I made some calls today.

22:00.192 --> 22:03.761
A private defense attorney is $300 an hour

22:03.796 --> 22:06.564
plus an up-front retainer of $10,000

22:06.599 --> 22:09.334
for investigators and interviews.

22:09.368 --> 22:12.570
So, they give you an idea
what the total would be?

22:12.605 --> 22:15.573
Well, if Antonio's case is resolved quickly,

22:15.608 --> 22:19.177
it could be $15,000, $20,000.

22:19.211 --> 22:23.781
It could be $50,000,
$100,000. I don't even know.

22:23.816 --> 22:27.318
[Dog barks in distance]

22:27.353 --> 22:30.688
I showed Raul Seravia my shop today.

22:30.723 --> 22:32.523
- What?
- Yeah.

22:32.558 --> 22:34.492
- Did he make you an offer?
- Yeah. Yeah.

22:34.526 --> 22:36.527
But not a good one.

22:36.562 --> 22:38.696
I need the money.

22:38.731 --> 22:41.332
God, I... up.

22:41.367 --> 22:42.700
[Sighs]

22:42.735 --> 22:43.801
No, <i>carnal.</i>

22:43.836 --> 22:47.038
Y-you just did what you
thought was right for Tony.

22:47.072 --> 22:49.774
But it didn't help him.

22:49.808 --> 22:51.609
I didn't save him.

22:54.814 --> 22:58.283
Look, let me talk to Raul, all right?

22:58.317 --> 22:59.851
I mean, he's a good businessman,

22:59.885 --> 23:01.186
but he's a good man, too.

23:01.220 --> 23:04.422
And...

23:04.457 --> 23:07.625
There's some lawyers that we
do some advocacy work with.

23:07.660 --> 23:09.761
They might not charge you so much up front.

23:12.298 --> 23:15.834
[Speaks Spanish]

23:15.868 --> 23:18.269
Okay, you can talk to him.

23:26.479 --> 23:28.480
[Indistinct conversations]

23:56.275 --> 23:59.711
[Indistinct shouting]

23:59.745 --> 24:02.781
Crowd chanting: "Free Carter Nix!"

24:05.251 --> 24:07.218
[Metal detectors beeping]

24:07.253 --> 24:09.888
Crowd chanting: "Justice for all!"

24:24.270 --> 24:26.838
Bailiff: All rise.

24:26.872 --> 24:30.642
The honorable judge days presiding.

24:30.676 --> 24:32.644
Please be seated.

24:32.678 --> 24:34.212
Where's Mark?

24:34.246 --> 24:35.847
Judge days: This is the time and place set

24:35.881 --> 24:38.049
for the preliminary examination in the case

24:38.084 --> 24:40.251
of the state of California vs. Carter Nix,

24:40.286 --> 24:43.188
case number A154231.

24:43.222 --> 24:44.823
Mr. Nix is present.

24:44.857 --> 24:46.825
Are all counsel ready to proceed?

24:46.859 --> 24:48.393
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Yes, Your Honor.

24:48.427 --> 24:50.195
I would like for it to be understood

24:50.229 --> 24:52.230
that these proceedings are to determine

24:52.264 --> 24:55.233
whether probable cause
exists to bind Mr. Nix

24:55.267 --> 24:57.035
for trial for capital murder.

24:57.069 --> 24:59.070
Based on the tangled route
this case has traveled,

24:59.105 --> 25:01.272
both the prosecution and the defense

25:01.307 --> 25:02.907
have a lot to prove.

25:02.942 --> 25:05.110
Although both sides would clearly like

25:05.144 --> 25:06.911
a speedy resolution to this hearing,

25:06.946 --> 25:08.013
because of the profile of this case,

25:08.047 --> 25:11.116
I intend to take my time
in weighing the evidence.

25:11.150 --> 25:12.517
Is that clear?

25:12.551 --> 25:14.285
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Yes, Your Honor.

25:14.320 --> 25:15.920
Call your first witness.

25:15.955 --> 25:17.088
[Man coughs]

25:17.123 --> 25:20.358
The people call Hector Tontz.

25:22.728 --> 25:26.097
[Door opens, closes]

25:34.974 --> 25:36.574
[Man coughs]

25:36.609 --> 25:37.475
You do solemnly swear

25:37.510 --> 25:39.144
that the testimony you are about to give

25:39.178 --> 25:40.745
in the matter now pending before this court

25:40.780 --> 25:42.113
shall be the truth, the whole truth,

25:42.148 --> 25:44.115
and nothing but the truth, so help you God?

25:44.150 --> 25:45.550
Yes, ma'am.

25:45.584 --> 25:48.019
Please take the stand and be seated.

25:50.956 --> 25:52.924
State your full name

25:52.958 --> 25:54.926
and spell your last name
for the record, please.

25:54.960 --> 25:57.128
Hector Tontz.

25:57.163 --> 26:02.000
T-o-n-t-z.

26:02.034 --> 26:06.504
Rick: Mr. Tontz, on
September 15th of last year

26:06.539 --> 26:09.741
at 11:45 in the evening,
were you in the location

26:09.775 --> 26:13.945
of 5608 Lombard Avenue in Modesto?

26:13.979 --> 26:15.947
Yes.

26:15.981 --> 26:17.348
I was cruising around that night

26:17.383 --> 26:21.853
and... I got a text from Carter Nix.

26:21.887 --> 26:25.323
And what did that text say?

26:25.357 --> 26:27.559
[Heart beating]

26:37.987 --> 26:39.760
[Buzzer]

26:39.760 --> 26:41.425
[Door opens]

26:45.341 --> 26:47.215
[Door closes]

27:10.600 --> 27:11.967
Ms. Taylor.

27:12.001 --> 27:13.168
Who are you?

27:13.202 --> 27:16.338
Tim Little, Carter's attorney.

27:16.372 --> 27:18.340
How is he?

27:18.374 --> 27:22.177
He does all right.

27:22.211 --> 27:26.348
Uh, w-w-what happened at that hearing thing?

27:26.382 --> 27:29.584
He asked me to handdeliver this to you.

27:29.619 --> 27:32.721
[Paper slides]

27:45.034 --> 27:47.836
- What is this bull...
- I'm sorry.

27:47.870 --> 27:50.639
I want to see him. No,
I-I want to see Carter.

27:50.673 --> 27:51.840
- Stop.
- He would never do this!

27:51.874 --> 27:52.741
- Hands off!
- He... he promised!

27:52.775 --> 27:54.342
- Calm down. Calm down.
- Please! Please!

27:54.377 --> 27:55.543
You made him do this.

27:55.578 --> 27:57.278
- Calm down.
- No, you can't!

27:57.313 --> 28:00.015
[Door opens] Get off me! Aah!

28:00.049 --> 28:03.184
[Grunts] Calm down! Hey, just relax!

28:03.219 --> 28:05.987
[Breathing heavily] Carter.

28:12.695 --> 28:15.063
[Insects chirping]

28:15.097 --> 28:16.331
Russ: F-forgive the mess.

28:16.365 --> 28:18.166
Mm-hmm.

28:18.200 --> 28:20.735
[Breathes deeply]

28:20.770 --> 28:22.737
It's really coming along.

28:22.772 --> 28:25.173
Yeah. I'm, uh... I'm getting there.

28:25.207 --> 28:27.375
Um... is there...

28:27.410 --> 28:30.178
I-is there any indication
at all from the judge?

28:30.212 --> 28:32.180
No, she meant what she said.

28:32.214 --> 28:34.549
- She's gonna take her time with it.
- Mm.

28:34.583 --> 28:38.553
[Sighs]

28:38.587 --> 28:41.356
What?

28:41.390 --> 28:43.992
Did you know Barb bought a gun?

28:44.026 --> 28:45.994
A gun? No.

28:46.028 --> 28:47.996
Really?

28:48.030 --> 28:48.797
[Stammers]

28:48.831 --> 28:50.198
If there's one person in the world

28:50.232 --> 28:51.766
who should not have a gun, it's Barb.

28:51.801 --> 28:54.569
When this all plays out,
Carter could be released.

28:54.603 --> 28:56.671
- Oh, I doubt, uh, that.
- It's possible.

28:56.706 --> 29:00.241
Barb, she's... she's an intense person,

29:00.276 --> 29:03.278
but Barb... I mean, she'd
never shoot anybody.

29:03.312 --> 29:05.680
- No, no, no.
- I mean, she just - she wouldn't.

29:05.715 --> 29:10.085
I'm not worried about her
shooting someone else.

29:10.119 --> 29:12.253
Well...

29:12.288 --> 29:14.255
I mean, no, obviously she's upset,

29:14.290 --> 29:17.092
but...

29:17.126 --> 29:20.295
She's... I mean, she's not like that.

29:20.329 --> 29:24.065
Well, I never thought I
was like that, either.

29:24.100 --> 29:25.467
When the man who killed my daughter

29:25.501 --> 29:26.434
got that joke of a sentence,

29:26.469 --> 29:29.437
I bought a gun, taught myself how to use it.

29:29.472 --> 29:31.272
To kill?

29:33.309 --> 29:35.276
I picked out a spot where my husband

29:35.311 --> 29:37.479
wouldn't be the first person to find me,

29:37.513 --> 29:40.081
somewhere outside where
I wouldn't make a mess.

29:40.116 --> 29:42.450
Had music on my iPod.

29:42.485 --> 29:46.421
I really, uh... I-I set it up good.

29:46.455 --> 29:48.823
I can't see you as that kind of person.

29:48.858 --> 29:50.425
What's the type?

29:50.459 --> 29:52.460
What's the type, except you can't stand

29:52.495 --> 29:54.462
what you're going through anymore?

29:54.497 --> 29:57.265
You know, it w... it was so easy

29:57.299 --> 29:59.434
to put that gun up to my chin,

29:59.468 --> 30:02.270
easy right up to pulling the trigger.

30:02.304 --> 30:03.438
But you have to be strong to do that.

30:03.472 --> 30:06.207
I wasn't. Barb is.

30:08.511 --> 30:13.114
Have you, um...

30:13.149 --> 30:15.316
H-have you talked to Barb about this?

30:15.351 --> 30:16.918
No.

30:16.952 --> 30:19.521
Uh, you should.

30:19.555 --> 30:21.756
I don't think it's my place.

30:26.162 --> 30:27.562
Our, um...

30:30.366 --> 30:33.768
Our lives weren't always this bad.

30:36.172 --> 30:39.941
S-s-she should remember that.

30:39.976 --> 30:41.977
Then maybe you should remind her.

30:44.513 --> 30:46.681
You're doing a good thing here.

30:46.716 --> 30:48.883
Hmm.

30:53.189 --> 30:56.358
Aubry: Just get Carter's lawyer.

30:56.392 --> 30:58.259
- Ruth: No.
- I just need a few minutes with him.

30:58.294 --> 31:00.261
- I won't do it.
- Where's dad?

31:00.296 --> 31:01.830
Oh, "dad." When you need him, it's "dad."

31:01.864 --> 31:03.264
- And when you don't...
- Please.

31:03.299 --> 31:06.267
I need Carter to tell me
why he tore the picture.

31:06.302 --> 31:08.637
- Why do you think?
- I need him to tell me why.

31:08.671 --> 31:11.840
He's done with you.

31:11.874 --> 31:16.044
I'll never ask you for anything ever again.

31:16.078 --> 31:18.046
- I swear to God.
- It's not healthy.

31:18.080 --> 31:21.916
- Please.
- I believe that, you father, Carter's sister...

31:26.389 --> 31:28.590
You talked to Aliyah?

31:32.528 --> 31:34.529
Did you talk to Carter?

31:38.100 --> 31:41.236
You talked to Carter, and he did this.

31:41.270 --> 31:44.606
It's for the best.

31:46.909 --> 31:48.877
I want to talk to my lawyer.

31:48.911 --> 31:50.879
He will not facilitate any communication

31:50.913 --> 31:52.313
between you and Carter whatsoever.

31:52.348 --> 31:54.315
I'm gonna send Carter a message.

31:56.552 --> 31:59.521
I want to see someone from the D.A.'s office

31:59.555 --> 32:02.357
and that detective.

32:02.391 --> 32:04.159
Bring them all in here.

32:12.529 --> 32:14.129
We appreciate you wanting to work with us.

32:14.197 --> 32:15.331
But based on your prior exhibitions,

32:15.398 --> 32:16.932
we would like to get
directly to your testimony.

32:17.000 --> 32:19.201
If the things you tell us have value,

32:19.269 --> 32:21.971
then we'd still be open to a plea agreement.

32:26.142 --> 32:28.777
This is the gun used to kill Matt Skokie.

32:28.845 --> 32:30.679
Hector Tontz testified

32:30.747 --> 32:33.015
that Carter Nix had it in his possession.

32:33.083 --> 32:36.785
Did Carter use this to murder Matt Skokie?

32:36.853 --> 32:38.787
That's the gun.

32:41.191 --> 32:43.192
But Carter didn't use it.

32:45.495 --> 32:46.796
I used it.

32:46.863 --> 32:49.598
I shot Matt. I shot his wife.

32:49.666 --> 32:51.067
- Ohh.
- Hold on.

32:51.134 --> 32:52.501
- Michael: What are you doing?
- I shot them.

32:52.569 --> 32:53.536
Stop it. Stop this.

32:53.603 --> 32:54.537
I need a moment alone with my client.

32:54.604 --> 32:55.504
- Ruth: She's lying.
- I'm not lying.

32:55.572 --> 32:56.739
Listen to me. Let me help you, please.

32:56.807 --> 32:57.940
She's an habitual liar.
This is what she does.

32:58.008 --> 32:58.974
Rick: No, no, no. Get
something to record this.

32:59.042 --> 33:01.344
Michael: Aubry, stop it. Aubry, please.

33:01.411 --> 33:02.745
I'm telling them what I'm telling them.

33:02.813 --> 33:05.014
- Warren: I advise you not to.
- I don't care what you advise.

33:05.082 --> 33:06.582
I'm telling them what I'm telling them.

33:06.650 --> 33:08.184
If you do this, I am done with you.

33:08.251 --> 33:09.518
- I mean it. I'm done.
- Oh, then go.

33:09.586 --> 33:11.187
My client is obviously distraught.

33:11.254 --> 33:12.388
Just give us two minutes alone to discuss...

33:12.456 --> 33:14.190
- Can I fire him?
- Ruth: You're being foolish.

33:14.257 --> 33:15.758
- Oh, you can go, too.
- Rick: He works for you.

33:15.826 --> 33:17.360
You're fired.

33:17.427 --> 33:19.962
You're done. Get out.

33:24.334 --> 33:27.436
[Sighs] Just go.

33:29.907 --> 33:33.442
Michael. [Sighs]

33:33.510 --> 33:37.780
[Inhales deeply] I'm staying.

33:39.516 --> 33:41.450
[Door closes]

33:47.257 --> 33:49.158
[Beep]

33:49.226 --> 33:50.826
[Clears throat]

33:50.894 --> 33:53.262
The statement of Aubry
Taylor is taking place

33:53.330 --> 33:55.531
at the Stanislaus County Psychiatric Center.

33:55.599 --> 33:58.067
Present are Deputy District
Attorney Soderbergh

33:58.135 --> 33:59.569
and myself, Detective Quinn.

33:59.636 --> 34:01.571
- Aubry Taylor's mother...
- Ruth.

34:01.638 --> 34:03.606
Ruth is also a witness.

34:03.674 --> 34:05.675
Ms. Taylor has previously
been advised of her rights

34:05.742 --> 34:07.977
and has waived the right
to have counsel present.

34:08.045 --> 34:09.579
Is that correct, Ms. Taylor?

34:09.646 --> 34:10.780
Yes.

34:10.847 --> 34:14.016
All right, Aubry, let's
start at the beginning.

34:14.083 --> 34:16.652
You have specific
information to share with us

34:16.719 --> 34:19.422
regarding the events of
September 15th of last year.

34:19.489 --> 34:21.623
Yes.

34:21.692 --> 34:24.060
Carter Nix went to this one dealer's house.

34:24.127 --> 34:26.128
- The dealer's name?
- Matt Skokie.

34:26.196 --> 34:27.797
Do you know his address?

34:27.864 --> 34:30.833
- Somewhere on Lombard.
- 5608 Lombard Avenue?

34:30.900 --> 34:32.101
I guess.

34:32.168 --> 34:35.438
Mm-hmm. For what reason did
Mr. Nix go to this address?

34:35.505 --> 34:36.906
Carter went to score drugs.

34:36.974 --> 34:38.574
And Hector Tontz drove him.

34:38.641 --> 34:40.409
I guess.

34:40.476 --> 34:41.643
What happened?

34:41.712 --> 34:43.980
Tried to negotiate, got hectic.

34:44.047 --> 34:45.648
Carter was short on funds,

34:45.716 --> 34:48.985
so Skokie told him he'd give
him drugs if I blew him.

34:49.052 --> 34:50.119
Carter was like... that.

34:50.187 --> 34:53.356
Stole some cash, credit cards, took off.

34:53.422 --> 34:54.556
But you weren't there?

34:54.625 --> 34:55.625
No.

34:55.692 --> 34:59.362
Hmm. What happened next?

34:59.429 --> 35:01.097
Carter comes back,

35:01.164 --> 35:06.068
tells me how Matt Skokie
was all "(Muted) this"

35:06.136 --> 35:11.474
and "(Muted) that,"
"(Muted)... your white bitch."

35:12.876 --> 35:15.211
Carter didn't do anything.

35:15.279 --> 35:18.281
He's too cool to care.

35:18.348 --> 35:20.783
He tells me what this
racist bastard's saying,

35:20.851 --> 35:23.052
so <i>I</i> went to settle.

35:23.120 --> 35:25.388
You went to 5608 Lombard Avenue?

35:25.456 --> 35:27.523
Whatever the address was,
it was Skokie's place.

35:27.591 --> 35:29.025
At what time?

35:29.093 --> 35:31.194
11:45... around there.

35:31.261 --> 35:34.030
Alone? On foot?

35:34.098 --> 35:35.598
You couldn't have made it from your place

35:35.666 --> 35:38.000
to the crime scene to fire
a shot in that time frame.

35:38.068 --> 35:39.836
Weren't at our place.

35:39.903 --> 35:42.405
We were shacking the night
with this dude, Everett.

35:42.473 --> 35:44.841
Everett's got some pieces laying around.

35:44.908 --> 35:47.643
Him, Carter are passed out.

35:47.711 --> 35:51.047
I'm like, "I'm gonna go
get some business handled."

35:51.115 --> 35:53.282
- I took the gun.
- Carter's gun.

35:53.350 --> 35:55.485
- Everett's gun.
- Rick: Where do we find Everett?

35:55.552 --> 35:57.520
Hell if I know. The guy floats.

35:57.588 --> 36:00.123
If you find him, I can I.D. him.

36:00.190 --> 36:01.891
Did you take this gun with you

36:01.959 --> 36:05.361
with the intent to shoot
either Mr. Skokie or his wife?

36:05.429 --> 36:09.332
Only for protection. That guy was violent.

36:09.399 --> 36:10.967
I wanted it if things got out of hand,

36:11.034 --> 36:12.468
which they did, big time.

36:12.536 --> 36:15.304
Keep going.

36:15.372 --> 36:18.174
I swapped sex for drugs with Matt before,

36:18.242 --> 36:20.276
so I used that to get back in.

36:20.344 --> 36:22.245
Mr. Skokie let you back into his home?

36:22.312 --> 36:23.613
Yeah.

36:23.680 --> 36:27.216
His wife wasn't putting out...
Not for him, anyway...

36:27.284 --> 36:29.085
So he was always pretty hard up.

36:29.153 --> 36:30.987
An easy play.

36:31.054 --> 36:33.789
Matt and me started
negotiating all over again.

36:33.857 --> 36:36.058
Was there sexual contact?

36:36.126 --> 36:39.829
Was there...? That the question?

36:39.897 --> 36:43.699
Yeah, he was for sure trying to get some.

36:43.767 --> 36:46.202
Then his wife came in,
screaming her head off.

36:46.270 --> 36:47.637
This was Gwen Skokie?

36:47.704 --> 36:49.839
Matt was real rough with her.

36:49.907 --> 36:51.741
Practically wrung her arm off

36:51.808 --> 36:53.910
flinging her back into the bedroom.

36:53.977 --> 36:56.412
Bruised her arms up.

36:56.480 --> 36:58.648
Mm, I hate seeing guys do women like that.

36:58.715 --> 37:00.149
I've been on the bad end of enough of that.

37:00.217 --> 37:03.186
So I tried to split.

37:03.253 --> 37:05.454
Matt wouldn't let me.

37:05.522 --> 37:07.423
He wouldn't let you leave?

37:07.491 --> 37:09.859
[Voice breaking] No.

37:09.927 --> 37:12.862
He wrung my arm, just like he did with her.

37:12.930 --> 37:16.399
When I fought back, h-he punched me,

37:16.466 --> 37:20.636
shoved me down, s-started
tearing my clothes off.

37:20.704 --> 37:22.905
[Scoffs]

37:22.973 --> 37:25.441
It was like my brother and his friends

37:25.509 --> 37:28.511
attacking me all over again.

37:28.579 --> 37:30.580
So I fought back the only way I could.

37:30.647 --> 37:33.015
Which was how?

37:33.083 --> 37:36.085
I shot him in the face.

37:36.153 --> 37:40.489
I didn't mean to do it. It was self-defense.

37:40.557 --> 37:41.857
When his wife heard the shot,

37:41.925 --> 37:43.259
she came running out of the bedroom at me

37:43.327 --> 37:45.061
with something in her hands.

37:45.128 --> 37:47.430
Do you know what that was?

37:47.497 --> 37:50.633
All I knew was it was big
and gnarly enough to kill me,

37:50.701 --> 37:53.436
so I...

37:53.503 --> 37:56.138
I shot her, too.

37:58.408 --> 38:00.276
Then I split.

38:00.344 --> 38:02.545
Took the gun, threw in in the Merced River.

38:02.613 --> 38:04.847
That's where you found it...
Somewhere around there, right?

38:04.915 --> 38:07.650
[Breathes deeply]

38:09.486 --> 38:12.388
Went to a liquor store, got a PBR.

38:12.456 --> 38:15.524
They probably got a video
of me or something.

38:15.592 --> 38:18.160
[Sighs]

38:23.934 --> 38:25.968
[Beep]

38:30.641 --> 38:32.642
[Knock on door]

38:37.047 --> 38:38.748
Hey. What?

38:38.815 --> 38:41.417
Uh, can I come in for a minute?

38:41.485 --> 38:42.752
You know where this goes.

38:42.819 --> 38:43.819
Just for a minute.

38:43.887 --> 38:46.022
I found some photos at Matt's house

38:46.089 --> 38:48.291
I want to show you.

38:48.358 --> 38:52.428
It's like looking at pictures
of somebody else's family.

38:52.496 --> 38:56.065
It wasn't all bad.

38:56.133 --> 38:58.634
No.

39:01.471 --> 39:04.440
Part of my 12-step for my gambling addiction

39:04.508 --> 39:06.609
was to admit fault for the mistakes I made.

39:06.677 --> 39:09.378
- Okay.
- Can you ever accept that?

39:09.446 --> 39:11.013
I can't even understand it.

39:11.081 --> 39:14.717
You're the one that started me gambling.

39:14.785 --> 39:17.420
F-first time I ever gambled with you...

39:17.487 --> 39:21.424
Quarters at video poker at
the California Hotel in Vegas.

39:21.491 --> 39:22.525
Yes.

39:22.592 --> 39:24.960
And from that dollar, I got you addicted.

39:25.028 --> 39:29.498
No. Well, I-I was sitting
there with you all night.

39:29.566 --> 39:32.968
You could take $20 and turn it
into eight hours of gambling.

39:33.036 --> 39:34.537
It was just meant to be fun.

39:34.604 --> 39:36.072
It's always fun when you're winning.

39:36.139 --> 39:38.474
You never understood
how to play the machines.

39:38.542 --> 39:39.642
You'd get these random draws,

39:39.710 --> 39:42.044
and you'd always hold the kicker.

39:42.112 --> 39:43.979
You can't play a double-double bonus

39:44.047 --> 39:46.215
like it was a deuces wild.

39:46.283 --> 39:48.751
That's the Barb I love.

39:48.819 --> 39:51.954
Video poker and an all-night buffet...

39:52.022 --> 39:53.756
That's all she needed.

39:56.360 --> 39:59.261
Oh, we could have had fun.

40:01.765 --> 40:03.532
But you got greedy with your gambling.

40:03.600 --> 40:05.334
- Not greedy.
- Yeah, you were greedy.

40:05.402 --> 40:06.702
You wanted to win all the time.

40:06.770 --> 40:08.804
That's not how gambling addiction works.

40:08.872 --> 40:10.539
It's not about the money.

40:10.607 --> 40:14.076
You lost enough of it. You stole enough.

40:14.144 --> 40:16.479
You know, I'm at the tables...
Forget video poker.

40:16.546 --> 40:18.314
I'm at the tables and the
dealer's got an ace showing.

40:18.382 --> 40:20.816
You're supposed to play like
he's got a face in the hole.

40:20.884 --> 40:22.618
I just know I can bust him

40:22.686 --> 40:25.254
or watch him turn a 7, then draw a 3

40:25.322 --> 40:26.822
on the crap pair of 8s I'm holding

40:26.890 --> 40:28.257
and collect.

40:28.325 --> 40:32.027
I'm sitting there, money on the felt,

40:32.095 --> 40:34.296
and I know I can do it...
Same with roulette.

40:34.364 --> 40:35.965
Every other sucker's placing wide,

40:36.032 --> 40:38.033
I lay the action numbers.

40:38.101 --> 40:41.737
And I can make the ball land winner.

40:41.805 --> 40:43.272
<i>Make</i> it land.

40:43.340 --> 40:44.707
Now they're sliding over my chips.

40:44.775 --> 40:46.842
Don't matter if it's $10 or $10 million.

40:46.910 --> 40:49.645
I did that.

40:49.713 --> 40:52.748
The universe, the odds,

40:52.816 --> 40:56.051
everything that said it couldn't happen...

40:56.119 --> 40:58.254
<i>I</i> made it happen.

40:58.321 --> 41:00.256
- Control.
- Mm.

41:00.323 --> 41:03.259
No, good Russ Skokie has all
the power in the universe

41:03.326 --> 41:07.263
to make the ball drop black 13.

41:07.330 --> 41:09.532
And I felt that way before I got sober.

41:09.599 --> 41:12.735
You can't control the universe.

41:12.803 --> 41:15.671
You can't even control what's going on here.

41:20.110 --> 41:22.778
Matt needed you, and you weren't here.

41:29.319 --> 41:32.822
And I have to live with that.

41:32.889 --> 41:35.758
We all have to live with
the things we've done.

41:35.826 --> 41:38.427
We got to live, Barb.

41:45.235 --> 41:49.071
I'm grateful for all you
did for Matt and Mark.

41:49.139 --> 41:50.506
I know it wasn't easy...

41:50.574 --> 41:53.509
All the tough choices you had to make.

41:55.912 --> 41:59.215
But whatever good things the boys had,

41:59.283 --> 42:01.784
they had because of you.

42:04.788 --> 42:06.889
Remember that.

42:14.598 --> 42:15.531
[Door opens, closes]

